  "Strong vs. Weak Acids/Bases": "",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "",
  "An example of a weak base is:": "",
  "Ammonia (NH₃) is a weak base — it partially reacts with water: NH₃ + H₂O ⇌ NH₄⁺ + OH⁻.": "",
  "The percentage ionization of a weak acid in 0.1 M solution is typically:": "",
  "Weak acids only partially ionize; typical % ionization for 0.1 M weak acids is 1–5% depending on Ka.": ""
